## Session Management — Vercel Serverless

Vercel runs multiple instances; in-process session stores don't share state. This project uses a **dual-store strategy**:

1. `express-session` with Upstash Redis (or cookie store) for primary session
2. A **signed PKCE cookie** (`_pkce`) as fallback for callback state recovery

```javascript
// On login: store in BOTH session and signed cookie
setPkceCookie(res, { state, codeVerifier, redirectUri, nonce }, isProd());

// On callback: prefer session, fall back to cookie
const pkceData = req.session.oauthState === state
  ? req.session
  : readPkceCookie(req); // validates HMAC signature
```

## Auth Middleware Pattern

```javascript
// middleware/auth.js
function authenticateToken(req, res, next) {
  const { oauthTokens, user } = req.session;

  // 1. Check session has a valid user
  if (!user) return res.status(401).json({ error: 'unauthorized' });

  // 2. Check token not expired — attempt refresh if so
  if (oauthTokens && isTokenExpired(oauthTokens.access_token)) {
    return refreshAndContinue(req, res, next);
  }

  next();
}

function determineClientType(req) {
  // 'admin' | 'user' | 'local'
  return req.session.oauthType || req.session.clientType || 'local';
}
```

## Correlation IDs

Every auth request should carry a correlation ID for log tracing:

```javascript
const correlationId = req.headers['x-correlation-id'] || crypto.randomUUID();
req.correlationId = correlationId;
res.setHeader('x-correlation-id', correlationId);
// Include in all PingOne API calls as X-Request-ID or X-Correlation-ID header
```

## Security Checklist

- ✅ PKCE (S256) on every authorization code flow
- ✅ State parameter validated on every callback (CSRF protection)
- ✅ Nonce validated in id_token after callback (replay protection)
- ✅ Redirect URIs validated server-side before constructing auth URL
- ✅ Tokens stored in server-side session (BFF) — never in localStorage or response body
- ✅ Tokens stored in HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax cookies
- ✅ RFC 7009 token revocation on logout
- ✅ `SKIP_TOKEN_SIGNATURE_VALIDATION=false` enforced in production
- ✅ Admin session cleared before initiating user/customer login (prevents role confusion)
- ✅ Rate limiting on `/api/auth/*` endpoints
- ❌ Never use implicit flow
- ❌ Never log raw tokens — log only token type, expiry, and event type
- ❌ Never expose `client_secret` to the browser/frontend

